messages.user_message: What is the appropriate bed or platform temperature for 3D printing using fused deposition modeling with polylactic acid (PLA)?
messages.assistant_response:
The appropriate platform (bed) temperature for 3D printing using fused deposition modeling with polylactic acid (PLA) varies depending on the type of filler used in the PLA-based composite. Here are some examples from the document "Enhanced_Table_Data.html":

- PLA + Copper: 60°C
- PLA + Wood: 65°C
- PLA + hydroxypropyl methylcellulose (HPMC): 40°C
- PLA + microcrystalline cellulose (MCC): 60°C
- PLA + carbonised cellulose nanofibers (CCN): 70°C
- PLA + cellulose nanofibers (CNF): 60°C
- PLA + cellulose nanocrystal (CNC): 60°C
- PLA + Cork Powder: 60°C
- PLA + Hydroxyapatite (HA): 50°C

These temperatures are specific to the composites listed and may vary for other types of PLA-based materials. [Source: Enhanced_Table_Data.html]
